Steps.Message: Update at 06:47 - We can now confirm that all power in your area should be back on. The issue was caused by a faulty overhead cable, which our engineers have now diverted power around the fault. We're sorry that we have been unable to provide you with frequent updates like we usually would. Due to the impact that Storm Bella has had on or network, we're dealing with a larger amount of faults than usual on our network. We know that being without power during the current pandemic can be especially difficult, especially over the festive period, so we're sorry for the outage. If your power isn't on or there's anything you'd like to talk to us about, call us on 08003163105 which is free from landlines and mobiles.

We became aware of this power cut at 04:04. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing

Steps.Message: All power in the area should be back on. We’re really sorry for any disruption this caused.
